div.div: feat: 增强文件上传功能，支持覆盖同名文件和处理上传冲突；优化上传进度面板和全局命令处理

feat: Refactor file management hooks and components for improved context menu handling and file operations
- Enhanced `useContextMenuHandler` to accept action handlers as parameters, simplifying context menu interactions. - Updated `useDirectoryUpload` to utilize external upload queue management, improving file upload handling. - Refactored `useFileActions` to support external upload queue integration and streamline file operations. - Introduced `useFileSelection` composable for managing file selection state, enabling multi-select functionality. - Implemented `useFileUploader` for managing file upload processes, including session handling and progress tracking. - Added utility functions in `fileUtils.ts` for path manipulation and URI extraction. - Updated `index.vue` to integrate new hooks and improve component interactions, including context menu and toolbar functionalities. - Enhanced UI feedback for file operations and improved code readability and maintainability.
feat: 更新子项目引用至新提交

feat: Refactor ID generation and decoding to unify public ID handling
- Updated user and group ID handling in user handler to use GeneratePublicID for consistency. - Refactored JWT authentication middleware to decode public IDs for user and user group. - Standardized public ID generation in auth service for user registration and password reset. - Enhanced file service to decode public file IDs and validate entity types. - Modified storage policy service to handle public IDs for policy retrieval and deletion. - Updated token service to generate and verify tokens using public IDs. - Removed specific user ID generation functions in idgen package, replacing them with a unified approach. - Improved comments and documentation for clarity and maintainability.

feat: Refactor file and user models, repositories, and storage entities
- Introduced FileType enum for file and directory types in the file model. - Enhanced File model with additional fields for metadata, source, and dimensions. - Removed the upload model and integrated its functionality into the file model. - Updated User model to remove UserID field and adjusted related repository methods. - Refactored FileRepository interface to use domain models instead of persistence objects. - Implemented CRUD operations in file repository with proper error handling and logging. - Added support for file storage entities with a new model for physical storage representation. - Improved ID generation with a unified public ID system for different entity types. - Enhanced JSON handling in the file persistence object for better metadata management.
